\n< Head Maid >Virginia-san?
\n< Serena >Yes...
\n< Serena >...Yes, what is it, Head Maid?

\n< Head Maid >The cleaning here is already sufficient.
Please move on to the next area.

\n< Head Maid >You must thoroughly clean the entire second
floor. It may be tough for a newcomer
like you, but please do it efficiently.
\n< Serena >Understood. I will start right away.
\n< Head Maid >Please.

\n< Serena >Cleaning the entire second floor, huh? That
works out well. While I work, I'll
search for the bathroom and unlock the
window.

\n< Serena >If I take too long, it might raise
suspicion. I'll finish quickly.

\n< Serena >Hm, there's a bit of dust left on this
window frame. I can't believe I
overlooked something like this...

\n< Serena >It is in these small details that one's
attitude is revealed. It's not about
whether someone sees it or not...
\n< Serena >......Dust, dust......dust, dust.......
\n< Head Maid >Virginia-san. Are you still here?
\n< Serena >Ah, Head Maid!?

\n< Serena >I'm sorry. I got completely absorbed in
cleaning...

\n< Head Maid >Since it's your first day, it would be good
for you to gradually get used to
managing your work schedule.

\n< Head Maid >Besides that, the preparations for lunch are
complete. Please come to the dining
hall.
\n< Head Maid >Let's all eat together.
\n< Serena >Understood.
\n< Head Maid >Virginia-san.

\n< Serena >Head Maid, I have finished cleaning. It's
perfect.

\n< Head Maid >...I see. You're quite fast. I will check if
there are any issues myself, so Serena,
please rest on the first floor until
mealtime.
\n< Serena >Understood. Well then, excuse me.

\n< Serena >Well, even if I'm told to rest... I guess
I'll do some information gathering to
prepare for tomorrow.

\n< Serena >Since I'll have to start working again as
soon as mealtime begins, I should
quickly finish the task while I have the
freedom to move around.

\n< Serena >...It seems that there hasn't been any
commotion. It appears that Cecilia
hasn't been found.

\n< Serena >However, now I don't know Cecilia's situation.
Did the commotion go as planned?

\n< Serena >...Wait. Don't act rashly. It wouldn't be good
to make any more mistakes.

\n< Serena >Besides, she might have left some signs. We need
to search for any traces carefully...
